@Andrew In general we’re talking about two different types of nouns.  Agent Nouns tend to end in “er” and “or”. Maker, Baker, Professor.    The person who does the the verb.   A baker bakes.

As opposed to a Recipient Noun.  The person who is being given something.  Employee as an example…vs Employer.

As for why someone chose to make it escapee…It was probably subjective in that an escapee perhaps was looked at as someone lower like an escaped criminal who really doesn’t have any power.   I guess to call them an escaper might imply it was their right and choice to escape.

